        "paragraph_index": 1,
        "text": "### Why This Gap Exists\n\nSRD-46 (NIST Critically Selected Stability Constants of Metal Complexes) is primarily a **room-temperature database**. The vast majority of its ~200,000+ measurements were made at or near **25 °C** in aqueous solution at atmospheric pressure. The database's temperature ceiling is only **81 °C**, and **pressure is not indexed at all** — most measurements are implicitly at 1 atm.",
        "claims": [
